3. Claim Processing Quest

Target stakeholders: EPFO staff, SSA/ASO/APFC/RPFC trainees, members
Game format: Case-solving game

The player acts as an EPFO claim processor. Different claims arrive: Form 19, Form 10C, Form 31, transfer claims, pension claims, death claims, EDLI claims.

The player must verify details, detect missing documents, check KYC, service history, nominee details, bank validation, and decide whether to approve, reject, or seek clarification.

Learning outcomes:

Staff learn claim scrutiny logic. Members learn why claims get rejected and how to avoid errors.

Example cases:

“Member applies for final PF withdrawal but exit date is missing.”
“Pension claim filed but service is below required threshold.”
“Death claim filed by nominee but nominee mismatch exists.”
“Bank account name differs from UAN name.”

Gamification:

Accuracy score, claim settlement time score, citizen satisfaction score, penalty for wrong rejection or wrong approval.
